#. Tag: title
#: importing-exporting.docbook:2
#, no-c-format
msgid "Importing and Exporting Data"
msgstr "Uvoz in izvoz podatkov"

#. Tag: para
#: importing-exporting.docbook:4
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"&appname; is able to import and export a wide variety of data files, as well "
"as search various Internet sites for information."
msgstr ""
"&appname; lahko uvaža in izvaža najrazličnejše podatkovne datoteke ter išče "
"informacije na različnih spletnih mestih."

#. Tag: title
#: importing-exporting.docbook:9
#, no-c-format
msgid "Importing from the Internet"
msgstr "Uvoz iz interneta"

#. Tag: para
#: importing-exporting.docbook:10
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"&appname; is able to search various Internet sites using the "
"<interface>Internet Search Dialog</interface>. Entries may be directly "
"imported and added to your current collection. The various providers are "
"configured via the <link linkend=\"data-sources-options\">Data Sources "
"Options</link>."
msgstr ""
"&appname; lahko išče po različnih internetnih straneh s pomočjo "
"<interface>Pogovorno okno za internetno iskanje</interface>. Vnose je mogoče "
"neposredno uvoziti in dodati vaši trenutni zbirki. Različni ponudniki so "
"konfigurirani prek <link linkend=\"data-sources-options\">Možnosti "
"podatkovnih virov</link>."

#. Tag: para
#: importing-exporting.docbook:14
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Searches may use different criteria: <guilabel>Title</guilabel>, "
"<guilabel>Person</guilabel>, <guilabel>ISBN</guilabel>, <guilabel>UPC/EAN</"
"guilabel>, <guilabel>LCCN</guilabel>, or <guilabel>Keyword</guilabel>. Not "
"all criteria are available for certain data sources. <acronym>ISBN</acronym> "
"and <acronym>LCCN</acronym> values are for books only, while <acronym>UPC</"
"acronym> or <acronym>EAN</acronym> values can apply to any type of item."
msgstr ""
"Iskanja lahko uporabljajo različne kriterije: <guilabel>Naziv</guilabel>, "
"<guilabel>Oseba</guilabel>, <guilabel>ISBN</guilabel>, <guilabel>UPC/EAN</"
"guilabel>, <guilabel>LCCN</guilabel> guilabel> ali <guilabel>Ključna beseda</"
"guilabel>. Za nekatere vire podatkov niso na voljo vsi kriteriji. Vrednosti "
"<acronym>ISBN</acronym> in <acronym>LCCN</acronym> sta samo za knjige, "
"vrednosti <acronym>UPC</acronym> ali <acronym>EAN</acronym> pa lahko veljajo "
"za katero koli vrsto predmeta."

#. Tag: para
#: importing-exporting.docbook:17
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Once a search is initiated, the <guibutton>Search</guibutton> button becomes "
"<guibutton>Stop</guibutton> which will end a search. As results are found, "
"they are added to the list directly under the search box, where selecting an "
"item will show the result without adding it to the collection. Clicking the "
"<guibutton>Add Entry</guibutton> button will add all the selected items to "
"your collection. If the data source has more results than were initially "
"requested, the <guibutton>Get More Results</guibutton> button becomes "
"active. Clicking <guibutton>Clear</guibutton> will remove all the current "
"results and reset the search."
msgstr ""
"Ko se iskanje začne, gumb <guibutton>Išči</guibutton> postane "
"<guibutton>Ustavi</guibutton>, kar bo končalo iskanje. Ko so rezultati "
"najdeni, so dodani na seznam neposredno pod iskalno polje, kjer se bo z "
"izbiro elementa prikazal rezultat, ne da bi ga dodali v zbirko. Če kliknete "
"gumb <guibutton>Dodaj vnos</guibutton>, boste v svojo zbirko dodali vse "
"izbrane elemente. Če ima vir podatkov več rezultatov, kot je bilo prvotno "
"zahtevanih, postane gumb <guibutton>Pridobi več rezultatov</guibutton> "
"aktiven. Če kliknete <guibutton>Počisti</guibutton>, boste odstranili vse "
"trenutne rezultate in ponastavili iskanje."

#. Tag: screeninfo
#: importing-exporting.docbook:21
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<screeninfo>The &appname; <interface>Internet Search Dialog</interface></"
"screeninfo>"
msgstr ""
"<screeninfo>&appname; <interface>Pogovorno okno internetnega iskanja</"
"interface></screeninfo>"

#. Tag: phrase
#: importing-exporting.docbook:24
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<phrase>The &appname; <interface>Internet Search Dialog</interface></phrase>"
msgstr ""
"<phrase>&appname; <interface>Pogovorno okno internetnega iskanja</"
"interface></phrase>"

#. Tag: para
#: importing-exporting.docbook:28
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Only entries that match the current collection type will be found. The "
"<guilabel>Description</guilabel> column provides additional information "
"about the entry, in order to differentiate between videos in different "
"formats, or books in different bindings, for example. Once an entry is "
"successfully added to the collection, a checkmark is added to the first "
"column in the list."
msgstr ""
"Najdeni bodo le vnosi, ki se ujemajo s trenutno vrsto zbirke. Stolpec "
"<guilabel>Opis</guilabel> vsebuje dodatne informacije o vnosu, da lahko na "
"primer razlikujete med videoposnetki v različnih formatih ali knjigami v "
"različnih vezavah. Ko je vnos uspešno dodan v zbirko, se prvemu stolpcu na "
"seznamu doda kljukica."

#. Tag: para
#: importing-exporting.docbook:32
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Multiple entries can be added at once by using the standard &kde; method for "
"multiple selection, which usually involves holding the &Shift; or &Ctrl; key "
"when clicking on an item."
msgstr ""
"Več vnosov je mogoče dodati hkrati z uporabo standardnega &kde; metoda za "
"večkratno izbiro, ki običajno vključuje držanje &Shift; ali &Ctrl; tipko ob "
"kliku na predmet."

#. Tag: para
#: importing-exporting.docbook:36
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"To facilitate the use of barcode scanners, searches can include multiple "
"ISBN/UPC values. Selecting the <guilabel>Multiple ISBN/UPC search</guilabel> "
"check box will disable the search box and enable the <guibutton>Edit ISBN/"
"UPC values...</guibutton> button, which will open a multi-line text entry "
"box. Each ISBN should be entered on a line by itself. After closing the box, "
"each ISBN will be validated for correct formatting. The ISBN validation is "
"able to convert 13-digit EAN values, as well as full <acronym>UPC</acronym> "
"codes, to the proper formatting. The ISBN list may also be read from a text "
"file."
msgstr ""
"Za lažjo uporabo čitalnikov črtne kode lahko iskanja vključujejo več "
"vrednosti ISBN/UPC. Če izberete potrditveno polje <guilabel>Iskanje po več "
"ISBN/UPC</guilabel>, boste onemogočili iskalno polje in omogočili gumb "
"<guibutton>Uredi vrednosti ISBN/UPC ...</guibutton>, ki bo odprl večvrstični "
"vnos besedila škatla. Vsak ISBN mora biti vnesen v vrstico zase. Ko zaprete "
"polje, bo vsak ISBN preverjen za pravilno oblikovanje. Preverjanje ISBN "
"lahko pretvori 13-mestne vrednosti EAN in polne <acronym>UPC</acronym> kode "
"v pravilno oblikovanje. Seznam ISBN je mogoče prebrati tudi iz besedilne "
"datoteke."

#. Tag: title
#: importing-exporting.docbook:43
#, no-c-format
msgid "Importing Data"
msgstr "Uvažanje podatkov"

#. Tag: para
#: importing-exporting.docbook:45
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"&appname; offers three different actions when importing data. "
"<guilabel>Replace current collection</guilabel> will close the current "
"collection, and create a new one with the data from the imported file. "
"<guilabel>Append to current collection</guilabel> tells &appname; to add all "
"the entries in the imported collection to the current one, and to add any "
"fields which don't currently exist. The <guilabel>Merge collection</"
"guilabel> action is the same as appending, except that each imported entry "
"is compared to the current ones, and any identical entries are skipped. "
"&appname; attempts to identify matching entries which are not completely "
"identical by comparing significant fields and will then merge the entries. "
"For example, music collections compare the artist and album, and the tracks "
"would be merged for matching entries. The <link linkend=\"importing-audio-"
"files\">audio file importer</link> is able to correctly build track lists by "
"merging entries."
msgstr ""
"&appname; ponuja tri različna dejanja pri uvozu podatkov. <guilabel>Zamenjaj "
"trenutno zbirko</guilabel> zapre trenutno zbirko in ustvari novo s podatki "
"iz uvožene datoteke. <guilabel>Dodaj trenutni zbirki</guilabel> pove "
"&appname; da dodate vse vnose v uvoženi zbirki v trenutno in dodate vsa "
"polja, ki trenutno ne obstajajo. Dejanje <guilabel>Združi zbirko</guilabel> "
"je enako kot pripenjanje, le da se vsak uvožen vnos primerja s trenutnimi, "
"vsi enaki vnosi pa so preskočeni. &appname; poskuša identificirati ujemajoče "
"se vnose, ki niso povsem identični, s primerjavo pomembnih polj in nato "
"združi vnose. Na primer, glasbene zbirke primerjajo izvajalca in album, "
"skladbe pa bi bile združene za ujemajoče se vnose. <link linkend=\"importing-"
"audio-files\">Uvoznik zvočnih datotek</link> lahko pravilno sestavi sezname "
"skladb z združevanjem vnosov."

#. Tag: title
#: importing-exporting.docbook:50
#, no-c-format
msgid "Importing Data From Other Software"
msgstr "Uvažanje podatkov iz druge programske opreme"

#. Tag: para
#: importing-exporting.docbook:52
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"&appname; can import data directly from a variety of other collection "
"management programs, including <application><ulink url=\"https://gitlab.com/"
"GCstar/GCstar\">GCstar</ulink></application>, <application><ulink url="
"\"https://onmyshelf.app\">OnMyShelf</ulink></application>, "
"<application><ulink url=\"https://www.datacrow.net/\">Data Crow</ulink></"
"application>, <application><ulink url=\"https://github.com/mvz/alexandria-"
"book-collection-manager\">Alexandria</ulink></application>, "
"<application><ulink url=\"https://www.delicious-monster.com\">Delicious "
"Library</ulink></application>, <application><ulink url=\"https://www."
"collectorz.com\">Collectorz</ulink></application>, <application><ulink url="
"\"http://www.antp.be/software/moviecatalog/\">Ant Movie Catalog</ulink></"
"application>, <application><ulink url=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/"
"Referencer\">Referencer</ulink></application>, and <application><ulink url="
"\"https://launchpad.net/griffith\">Griffith</ulink></application>."
msgstr ""
"&appname; lahko uvozi podatke neposredno iz različnih drugih programov za "
"upravljanje zbirk, vključno z <application><ulink url=\"https://gitlab.com/"
"GCstar/GCstar\">GCstar</ulink></application>, <application><ulink url="
"\"https://onmyshelf.app\">OnMyShelf</ulink></application>, "
"<application><ulink url=\"https://www.datacrow.net/\">Data Crow</ulink></"
"application>, <application><ulink url=\"https://github.com/mvz/alexandria-"
"book-collection-manager\">Alexandria</ulink></application>, "
"<application><ulink url=\"https://www.delicious-monster.com\">Delicious "
"Library</ulink></application>, <application><ulink url=\"https://www."
"collectorz.com\">Collectorz</ulink></application>, <application><ulink url="
"\"http://www.antp.be/software/moviecatalog/\">Ant Movie Catalog</ulink></"
"application>, <application><ulink url=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/"
"Referencer\">Referencer</ulink></application>, in <application><ulink url="
"\"https://launchpad.net/griffith\">Griffith</ulink></application>."

#. Tag: title
#: importing-exporting.docbook:66
#, no-c-format
msgid "Importing Other Data Formats"
msgstr "Uvažanje drugih formatov podatkov"

#. Tag: para
#: importing-exporting.docbook:67
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"&appname; can import data from a variety of other file formats, including "
"<acronym>CSV</acronym>, bibtex, audio discs and files, <acronym>MODS</"
"acronym>, &PDF;, and <acronym>RIS</acronym>."
msgstr ""
"&appname; lahko uvozi podatke iz različnih drugih formatov datotek, vključno "
"s <acronym>CSV</acronym>, bibtex, zvočnimi diski in datotekami, "
"<acronym>MODS</acronym>, &PDF; in <acronym>RIS</acronym>."

#. Tag: title
#: importing-exporting.docbook:70
#, no-c-format
msgid "Importing &appname; Data"
msgstr "Uvažanje podatkov &appname;"

#. Tag: para
#: importing-exporting.docbook:72
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Other &appname; data files may be imported directly. Replacing the current "
"collection by importing a &appname; file is the same thing as just opening "
"the file itself. The value of importing &appname; data is primarily for "
"appending or merging two collections together."
msgstr ""
"Druge podatkovne datoteke &appname; je mogoče uvoziti neposredno. Zamenjava "
"trenutne zbirke z uvozom &appname; datoteka je isto kot samo odpiranje "
"datoteke same. Vrednost uvoza &appname; podatkov je predvsem za dodajanje "
"ali združevanje dveh zbirk."

#. Tag: title
#: importing-exporting.docbook:78
#, no-c-format
msgid "Importing CSV Data"
msgstr "Uvažanje podatkov CSV"

#. Tag: para
#: importing-exporting.docbook:80
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Comma-separated values (<acronym>CSV</acronym>) are a common way of "
"importing and exporting tabular data. Each field value is separated by a "
"comma, with one entry per line. The field titles may be included in the "
"first line. The CSV importer is not limited to using a comma as the "
"separator. Any character or string may be used."
msgstr ""
"Z vejicami ločene vrednosti (<acronym>CSV</acronym>) so običajen način za "
"uvoz in izvoz tabelaričnih podatkov. Vsaka vrednost polja je ločena z "
"vejico, z enim vnosom na vrstico. Naslovi polj so lahko vključeni v prvo "
"vrstico. Uvoznik CSV ni omejen na uporabo vejice kot ločila. Uporabi se "
"lahko kateri koli znak ali niz."

#. Tag: screeninfo
#: importing-exporting.docbook:85
#, no-c-format
msgid "<screeninfo>The CSV Import Dialog</screeninfo>"
msgstr "<screeninfo>Pogovorno okno za uvoz CSV</screeninfo>"

#. Tag: phrase
#: importing-exporting.docbook:88
#, no-c-format
msgid "<phrase>The CSV Import Dialog</phrase>"
msgstr "<phrase>Pogovorno okno za uvoz CSV</phrase>"

#. Tag: para
#: importing-exporting.docbook:92
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"First, select the type of collection that you are importing. If you are "
"appending or merging to your open collection, the type is limited to your "
"current collection type. If the first line of the CSV file contains the "
"field titles, click the check box and the importer will automatically "
"compare the titles against the fields in the current collection. If a field "
"title matches, the header for that column changes to show that the column "
"has been assigned to that field. If the file uses a delimiter other than a "
"comma, be sure to change that option accordingly."
msgstr ""
"Najprej izberite vrsto zbirke, ki jo uvažate. Če dodajate ali združujete "
"svojo odprto zbirko, je vrsta omejena na vašo trenutno vrsto zbirke. Če prva "
"vrstica datoteke CSV vsebuje naslove polj, kliknite potrditveno polje in "
"uvoznik bo samodejno primerjal naslove s polji v trenutni zbirki. Če se "
"naslov polja ujema, se glava tega stolpca spremeni in pokaže, da je bil "
"stolpec dodeljen temu polju. Če datoteka uporablja ločilo, ki ni vejica, to "
"možnost ustrezno spremenite."

#. Tag: para
#: importing-exporting.docbook:96
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"In order for &appname; to properly import the file, it must know which field "
"corresponds to each column. <emphasis>If the column only has a number in the "
"header, the data in that column will not be imported.</emphasis> You should "
"assign fields to each column by selecting a column, either by clicking in it "
"or changing the column number itself, then selecting the field to assign "
"from the drop down box and clicking the <guibutton>Assign Field</guibutton> "
"button. If you need to add a new field to the collection, the last item in "
"the drop down box opens the <link linkend=\"fields-dialog"
"\"><interface>Collection Fields Dialog</interface></link>."
msgstr ""
"Za pravilen uvoz datoteke v &appname; mora aplikacija vedeti, katero polje "
"ustreza posameznemu stolpcu. <emphasis>Če ima stolpec samo številko v glavi, "
"podatki v tem stolpcu ne bodo uvoženi.</emphasis> Vsakemu stolpcu morate "
"dodeliti polja tako, da izberete stolpec, tako da ga kliknete ali spremenite "
"številko stolpca sam, nato pa iz spustnega menija izberete polje za "
"dodelitev in kliknete gumb <guibutton>Dodeli polje</guibutton>. Če morate v "
"zbirko dodati novo polje, zadnji element v spustnem polju odpre <link "
"linkend=\"fields-dialog\"><interface>Pogovorno okno Polja zbirke</"
"interface></link>."

#. Tag: para
#: importing-exporting.docbook:100
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"For compactness, only the first five lines of the imported CSV file are "
"shown in the dialog. However, all the lines in the file will be imported."
msgstr ""
"Zaradi kompaktnosti je v pogovornem oknu prikazanih samo prvih pet vrstic "
"uvožene datoteke CSV. Vendar bodo vse vrstice v datoteki uvožene."

#. Tag: title
#: importing-exporting.docbook:107
#, no-c-format
msgid "Importing Audio &CD; Data"
msgstr "Uvažanje zvoka &CD; podatki"

#. Tag: para
#: importing-exporting.docbook:109
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"&appname; is able to use the <ulink url=\"http://gnudb.org\">freedb.org</"
"ulink> service to lookup information about a &CD;, including the track list. "
"Depending on your distribution, settings for access to the service may be "
"set in the &kde; &systemsettings;. The &CD; artist, title, genre, year, and "
"track listing are all added."
msgstr ""
"&appname; lahko uporablja storitev <ulink url=\"http://gnudb.org\">freedb."
"org</ulink> za iskanje informacij o &CD;, vključno s seznamom skladb. "
"Odvisno od vaše distribucije lahko nastavitve za dostop do storitve "
"nastavite v &kde; &systemsettings;. &CD; dodani so izvajalec, naslov, zvrst, "
"leto in seznam skladb."

#. Tag: para
#: importing-exporting.docbook:116
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"In addition, if the disc contains &CD;-Text, that information is read and "
"added to the imported entry."
msgstr ""
"Poleg tega, če disk vsebuje &CD;-besedilo, se te informacije preberejo in "
"dodajo uvoženemu vnosu."

#. Tag: title
#: importing-exporting.docbook:122
#, no-c-format
msgid "Importing Audio File Metadata"
msgstr "Uvažanje metapodatkov zvočne datoteke"

#. Tag: para
#: importing-exporting.docbook:124
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"&appname; is able to scan a folder and read the tags for common audio file "
"formats, such as <literal role=\"extension\">mp3</literal> and <literal role="
"\"extension\">ogg</literal>. The songs are entered in a music collection, "
"where each entry is an album. If the song files contain the track number, "
"the song name is inserted in the correct spot in the track list. The artist "
"and genre information is also added to the entry. If the song tags contain "
"comments, they are appended to the comments field in the entry, preceded by "
"the file name."
msgstr ""
"&appname; lahko pregleda mapo in prebere oznake za pogoste formate zvočnih "
"datotek, kot sta <literal role=\"extension\">mp3</literal> in <literal role="
"\"extension\">ogg</literal>. Pesmi so vnesene v glasbeno zbirko, kjer je "
"vsak vnos album. Če datoteke pesmi vsebujejo številko skladbe, je ime "
"skladbe vstavljeno na pravo mesto na seznamu skladb. Vnosu so dodani tudi "
"podatki o izvajalcu in žanru. Če oznake pesmi vsebujejo komentarje, so "
"dodani v polje za komentarje v vnosu, pred katerim je ime datoteke."

#. Tag: para
#: importing-exporting.docbook:128
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"In addition, if a folder contains a <filename>.directory</filename> file and "
"the folder name matches an album title, the <literal>Icon</literal> entry in "
"the desktop file is used as the cover image for the album."
msgstr ""
"Poleg tega, če mapa vsebuje datoteko <filename>.directory</filename> in se "
"ime mape ujema z naslovom albuma, se vnos <literal>ikona</literal> v namizni "
"datoteki uporabi kot naslovna slika albuma ."

#. Tag: para
#: importing-exporting.docbook:132
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The audio file metadata importer can recursively scan a folder to find all "
"audio files in any subfolder, though symbolic links are not followed. "
"&appname; uses the <ulink url=\"https://taglib.org\">TagLib library</ulink> "
"for reading the audio file metadata, and so can import data from any file "
"type that TagLib understands."
msgstr ""
"Uvoznik metapodatkov zvočnih datotek lahko rekurzivno pregleda mapo, da "
"poišče vse zvočne datoteke v kateri koli podmapi, vendar simbolnim povezavam "
"ne sledi. &appname; uporablja <ulink url=\"https://taglib.org\">knjižnico "
"TagLib</ulink> za branje metapodatkov zvočne datoteke in tako lahko uvozi "
"podatke iz katere koli vrste datoteke, ki jo TagLib razume."

#. Tag: title
#: importing-exporting.docbook:139
#, no-c-format
msgid "Importing Bibtex Data"
msgstr "Uvažanje podatkov Bibtex"

#. Tag: para
#: importing-exporting.docbook:141
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<ulink url=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Bibtex\">Bibtex</ulink> is a "
"bibliography format used with the LaTeX document preparation system. Various "
"type of bibliographic references may be included in the file. &appname; "
"imports bibtex files as a <link linkend=\"bibliography\">Bibliographic "
"collection</link>."
msgstr ""
"<ulink url=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Bibtex\">Bibtex</ulink> je format "
"bibliografije, ki se uporablja s sistemom za pripravo dokumentov LaTeX. V "
"datoteko so lahko vključene različne vrste bibliografskih referenc. "
"&appname; uvozi datoteke bibtex kot <link linkend=\"bibliography"
"\">Bibliografsko zbirko</link>."

#. Tag: para
#: importing-exporting.docbook:145
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"If the bibtex importer encounters fields in the file which are not in the "
"default bibliography collection, they are added as <link linkend=\"line"
"\">Simple Text</link> fields, with two exceptions. If the field value "
"contains more than 100 characters, it becomes a <link linkend=\"para"
"\">Paragraph</link> field. If the field value appears to contain a &URL; or "
"a file reference, then a <link linkend=\"url\">&URL;</link> field is "
"created. &appname; uses an internal copy of the <ulink url=\"http://www.gerg."
"ca/software/btOOL/\">btparse library</ulink> for parsing the bibtex files."
msgstr ""
"Če uvoznik bibtex v datoteki naleti na polja, ki niso v privzeti "
"bibliografski zbirki, so dodana kot polja <link linkend=\"line\">Preprosto "
"besedilo</link>, z dvema izjemama. Če vrednost polja vsebuje več kot 100 "
"znakov, postane polje <link linkend=\"para\">Odstavek</link>. Če se zdi, da "
"vrednost polja vsebuje &URL; ali sklic na datoteko, potem se ustvari polje "
"<link linkend=\"url\">&URL;</link>. &appname; uporablja notranjo kopijo "
"<ulink url=\"http://www.gerg.ca/software/btOOL/\">knjižnice btparse</ulink> "
"za razčlenjevanje datotek bibtex."

#. Tag: para
#: importing-exporting.docbook:149
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<ulink url=\"http://bibtexml.sf.net\">Bibtexml</ulink> is an &XML; "
"representation of bibtex data, and the data from the imported bibtexml file "
"is treated in the same way as bibtex data would be."
msgstr ""
"<ulink url=\"http://bibtexml.sf.net\">Bibtexml</ulink> je &XML; predstavitev "
"podatkov bibtex, podatki iz uvožene datoteke bibtexml pa se obravnavajo na "
"enak način kot podatki bibtex."

#. Tag: title
#: importing-exporting.docbook:155
#, no-c-format
msgid "Importing MODS Data"
msgstr "Uvažanje podatkov MODS"

#. Tag: para
#: importing-exporting.docbook:157
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<acronym><ulink url=\"http://www.loc.gov/standards/mods/\">MODS</ulink></"
"acronym> is a format for representing various types of media collections. "
"Currently, only books are imported by &appname;, as a <link linkend="
"\"bibliography\">Bibliographic collection</link>."
msgstr ""
"<acronym><ulink url=\"http://www.loc.gov/standards/mods/\">MODS</ulink></"
"acronym> je format za predstavitev različnih vrst medijskih zbirk. Trenutno "
"&appname; uvaža samo knjige kot <link linkend=\"bibliography\">Bibliografsko "
"zbirko</link>."

#. Tag: title
#: importing-exporting.docbook:164
#, no-c-format
msgid "Importing &PDF; Data"
msgstr "Uvažanje &PDF; podatki"

#. Tag: para
#: importing-exporting.docbook:165
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"If &appname; was compiled with <emphasis>exempi</emphasis> or "
"<emphasis>poppler</emphasis> support, metadata from &PDF; files can be "
"imported. Metadata may include title, author, and date information, as well "
"as bibliographic identifiers which are then used to update other information."
msgstr ""
"Če &appname; je bil preveden s podporo za <emphasis>exempi</emphasis> ali "
"<emphasis>poppler</emphasis>, metapodatki iz &PDF; datoteke je mogoče "
"uvoziti. Metapodatki lahko vključujejo informacije o naslovu, avtorju in "
"datumu ter bibliografske identifikatorje, ki se nato uporabijo za "
"posodobitev drugih informacij."

#. Tag: title
#: importing-exporting.docbook:171
#, no-c-format
msgid "Importing RIS Data"
msgstr "Uvažanje podatkov RIS"

#. Tag: para
#: importing-exporting.docbook:172
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The <ulink url=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/"
"RIS_(file_format)\"><acronym>RIS</acronym> format</ulink> is a bibliographic "
"file format used by <application>EndNote</application>, "
"<application>Reference Manager</application>, and others. &appname; imports "
"RIS files as a <link linkend=\"bibliography\">Bibliographic collection</"
"link>."
msgstr ""
"Format <ulink url=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/"
"RIS_(file_format)\"><acronym>RIS</acronym></ulink> je bibliografski format "
"datoteke, ki ga uporablja <application>EndNote</application>, "
"<application>Reference Manager</application> in drugi. &appname; uvozi "
"datoteke RIS kot <link linkend=\"bibliography\">Bibliografsko zbirko</link>."

#. Tag: title
#: importing-exporting.docbook:180
#, no-c-format
msgid "Importing Online Collections"
msgstr "Uvažanje spletnih zbirk"

#. Tag: para
#: importing-exporting.docbook:181
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"&appname; can connect to and import from websites that manage personal "
"collections."
msgstr ""
"&appname; se lahko poveže in uvaža s spletnih mest, ki upravljajo osebne "
"zbirke."

#. Tag: title
#: importing-exporting.docbook:184
#, no-c-format
msgid "Importing BoardGameGeek Collection"
msgstr "Uvažanje zbirke BoardGameGeek"

#. Tag: para
#: importing-exporting.docbook:185
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<ulink url=\"https://boardgamegeek.com\">BoardGameGeek</ulink> is an online "
"board gaming resource and community. &appname; can import the board games in "
"a user's collection, as long as the collection is set to be publicly "
"accessible. The imported collection may be limited to those items marked as "
"being owned."
msgstr ""
"<ulink url=\"https://boardgamegeek.com\">BoardGameGeek</ulink> je spletni "
"vir in skupnost za družabne igre. &appname; lahko uvozi družabne igre v "
"uporabnikovi zbirki, če je zbirka nastavljena kot javno dostopna. Uvožena "
"zbirka je lahko omejena na predmete, ki so označeni kot lastniški."

#. Tag: title
#: importing-exporting.docbook:191
#, no-c-format
msgid "Importing Goodreads Collection"
msgstr "Uvažanje zbirke Goodreads"

#. Tag: para
#: importing-exporting.docbook:192
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<ulink url=\"https://www.goodreads.com\">Goodreads</ulink> is an online "
"social network for readers to track book collections. &appname; can import "
"the list of books in a user's collection, given either the user name or user "
"ID, as long as the collection is set to be publicly accessible."
msgstr ""
"<ulink url=\"https://www.goodreads.com\">Goodreads</ulink> je spletno "
"socialno omrežje za bralce, ki spremljajo knjižne zbirke. &appname; lahko "
"uvozi seznam knjig v uporabnikovi zbirki glede na uporabniško ime ali ID "
"uporabnika, če je zbirka nastavljena kot javno dostopna."

#. Tag: title
#: importing-exporting.docbook:198
#, no-c-format
msgid "Importing LibraryThing Collection"
msgstr "Uvažanje zbirke LibraryThing"

#. Tag: para
#: importing-exporting.docbook:199
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<ulink url=\"https://www.librarything.com\">LibraryThing</ulink> is an "
"online service to help people catalog their books easily. &appname; can "
"import the list of books in a user's collection, <ulink url=\"https://www."
"librarything.com/export.php?export_type=json\">exported in JSON format</"
"ulink>."
msgstr ""
"<ulink url=\"https://www.librarything.com\">LibraryThing</ulink> je spletna "
"storitev, ki ljudem pomaga enostavno katalogizirati svoje knjige. &appname; "
"lahko uvozi seznam knjig v uporabnikovi zbirki, <ulink url=\"https://www."
"librarything.com/export.php?export_type=json\">izvožen v formatu JSON</"
"ulink>."

#. Tag: title
#: importing-exporting.docbook:205
#, no-c-format
msgid "Importing Discogs Collection"
msgstr "Uvažanje zbirke Discogs"

#. Tag: para
#: importing-exporting.docbook:206
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<ulink url=\"https://www.discogs.com\">Discogs</ulink> is an online database "
"and marketplace of music releases. &appname; can import the list of music "
"releases in a user's collection, given the user name, as long as the "
"collection is set to be publicly accessible."
msgstr ""
"<ulink url=\"https://www.discogs.com\">Discogs</ulink> je spletna zbirka "
"podatkov in tržnica glasbenih izdaj. &appname; lahko uvozi seznam glasbenih "
"izdaj v uporabnikovi zbirki glede na uporabniško ime, če je zbirka "
"nastavljena kot javno dostopna."

#. Tag: title
#: importing-exporting.docbook:214
#, no-c-format
msgid "Importing File Listings"
msgstr "Uvažanje seznamov datotek"

#. Tag: para
#: importing-exporting.docbook:216
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"&tellico; can scan folders to import file information, primarily to create a "
"<link linkend=\"file-catalog\">File Catalog</link> collection. The folder "
"may be searched recursively, to add all files found within. This importer is "
"most useful for backup listings and media cataloging, such as &CD; or "
"<acronym>DVD</acronym> listings. In addition, image previews of the file "
"contents may be generated. The file previews are same as those shown in the "
"&kde; file manager."
msgstr ""
"&tellico; lahko prečeše mape za uvoz informacij o datotekah, predvsem za "
"ustvarjanjezbirke <link linkend=\"file-catalog\">Kataloga datotek</link>. "
"Mapo lahko preišče rekurzivno, da doda vse datoteke, ki jih najde znotraj. "
"Ta uvoznik je najbolj uporaben za varnostne kopije seznamov in "
"katalogizacijo medijev, kot so &CD; oz. seznami <acronym>DVD-jev</acronym>. "
"Poleg tega lahko ustvarijo slikovne predoglede datoteke vsebine. Predogledi "
"datotek so enaki tistim, prikazanim v &kde; upravljalniku datotek."

#. Tag: para
#: importing-exporting.docbook:220
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Folders with ebook files and video files may also be imported as book and "
"video collections. File metadata can be read, and for video files, any "
"existing <literal role=\"extension\">nfo</literal> files are used to "
"complete the video entry information."
msgstr ""
"Mape z datotekami e-knjig in video datotekami se lahko uvozijo tudi kot "
"knjige invideo zbirke. Metapodatke o datotekah je mogoče brati, za video "
"datoteke pa se uporabljajo poljubne obstoječe datoteke <literal role="
"\"extension\">nfo</literal>za izpolnjevanje podatkov o vnosu videa."

#. Tag: title
#: importing-exporting.docbook:227
#, no-c-format
msgid "Importing &XML; Data via XSLT"
msgstr "Uvažanje &XML; Podatki prek XSLT"

#. Tag: para
#: importing-exporting.docbook:229
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Any &XML; file may be imported into &appname; provided an &XSL; stylesheet "
"is available to convert the file to &appname; format. &appname; "
"automatically loads the stylesheet and performs the &xslt; processing needed "
"to load the file."
msgstr ""
"Vsak &XML; datoteko lahko uvozite v &appname; podal &XSL; za pretvorbo "
"datoteke v &appname; format. &appname; samodejno naloži slogovno datoteko in "
"izvede &xslt; potrebna obdelava za nalaganje datoteke."

#. Tag: title
#: importing-exporting.docbook:237
#, no-c-format
msgid "Drag and Drop"
msgstr "Povleci in spusti"

#. Tag: para
#: importing-exporting.docbook:239
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Dragging data files to the main &appname; window and dropping them will "
"import the files, just as if the <link linkend=\"importing\">import command</"
"link> was made from the menus. Drag and drop works for the following file "
"formats: Tellico, Bibtex, RIS, &PDF;, and EPub. Importing multiple files at "
"once is also supported."
msgstr ""
"Vlečenje podatkovnih datotek v glavno &appname; okno in jih spustite, bodo "
"uvozili datoteke, tako kot če bi bil <link linkend=\"importing\">ukaz za "
"uvoz</link> narejen iz menijev. Povleci in spusti deluje za naslednje "
"formate datotek: Tellico, Bibtex, RIS, &PDF; in EPub. Podprt je tudi uvoz "
"več datotek hkrati."

#. Tag: para
#: importing-exporting.docbook:241
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"So, for example, if you want to catalog several <link linkend=\"importing-pdf"
"\">&PDF; files</link>, select them in the file manager and drag them to the "
"&appname; window. &appname; will import as much metadata from the files as "
"it can, and then fetch additional information from various configured "
"Internet sources."
msgstr ""
"Torej, če želite na primer katalogizirati več <link linkend=\"importing-pdf"
"\">&PDF; datotek</link>, jih izberite v upravitelju datotek in jih povlecite "
"v &appname; okno. &appname; bo uvozil čim več metapodatkov iz datotek in "
"nato pridobil dodatne informacije iz različnih konfiguriranih internetnih "
"virov."

#. Tag: title
#: importing-exporting.docbook:246
#, no-c-format
msgid "Exporting Data"
msgstr "Izvažanje podatkov"

#. Tag: para
#: importing-exporting.docbook:248
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"When exporting the data in the collection, the entry values may be exported "
"as entered, or with the <link linkend=\"field-formatting\">automatic "
"formatting</link> provided by &appname;. Additionally, the export may be "
"limited to the currently selected entries of the collection as well, where "
"the <link linkend=\"status-bar\">statusbar</link> shows the number of "
"selected entries."
msgstr ""
"Pri izvozu podatkov v zbirki se lahko vnesene vrednosti izvozijo, kot so "
"vnesene, ali s <link linkend=\"field-formatting\">samodejnim oblikovanjem</"
"link>, ki ga zagotavlja &appname;. Poleg tega je lahko izvoz omejen tudi na "
"trenutno izbrane vnose v zbirki, kjer <link linkend=\"status-bar\">vrstica "
"stanja</link> prikazuje število izbranih vnosov."

#. Tag: para
#: importing-exporting.docbook:252
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Exported text files, such as Bibtex or CSV, may use the Unicode (UTF-8) "
"character encoding, or the current locale of the operating system."
msgstr ""
"Izvožene besedilne datoteke, kot sta Bibtex ali CSV, lahko uporabljajo "
"kodiranje znakov Unicode (UTF-8) ali trenutno področno nastavitev "
"operacijskega sistema."

#. Tag: screeninfo
#: importing-exporting.docbook:257
#, no-c-format
msgid "<screeninfo>General Export Options</screeninfo>"
msgstr "<screeninfo>Splošne možnosti izvoza</screeninfo>"

#. Tag: phrase
#: importing-exporting.docbook:260
#, no-c-format
msgid "<phrase>General Export Options</phrase>"
msgstr "<phrase>Splošne možnosti izvoza</phrase>"

#. Tag: title
#: importing-exporting.docbook:265
#, no-c-format
msgid "Exporting &XML;"
msgstr "Izvažanje &XML;"

#. Tag: para
#: importing-exporting.docbook:267
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The file format for &appname; data is a zipped &XML; file. Exporting to "
"&XML; merely creates the &XML; file without zipping it. Images may be "
"included in the &XML; file as base64-encoded data in an image element, but "
"doing so can create very large text files."
msgstr ""
"Format datoteke za &appname; podatki so stisnjeni &XML; mapa. Izvažanje v "
"&XML; samo ustvari &XML; datoteko, ne da bi jo stisnili. Slike so lahko "
"vključene v &XML; datoteko kot podatke, kodirane z base64, v slikovnem "
"elementu, vendar lahko s tem ustvarite zelo velike besedilne datoteke."

#. Tag: title
#: importing-exporting.docbook:273
#, no-c-format
msgid "Exporting Zip"
msgstr "Izvoz Zip"

#. Tag: para
#: importing-exporting.docbook:275
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The standard file format for &appname; is a zipped file, containing the "
"&XML; collection file, and optionally, all the images referenced in the "
"collection. If the images are being stored in the application folder "
"instead, exporting to a Zip file will create a self-contained data file, "
"which includes all the images in the collection."
msgstr ""
"Standardna oblika datoteke za &appname; je stisnjena zip datoteka, ki "
"vsebuje datoteko zbirke &XML; in po izbiri vse slike, na katere se sklicuje "
"zbirka. Če so slike shranjene v mapi aplikacije, bo izvoz v datoteko Zip "
"ustvaril samostojno podatkovno datoteko, ki vključuje vse slike v zbirki."

#. Tag: title
#: importing-exporting.docbook:281
#, no-c-format
msgid "Exporting &HTML;"
msgstr "Izvažanje &HTML;"

#. Tag: para
#: importing-exporting.docbook:283
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The &HTML; export uses the <filename>tellico2html.xsl</filename> stylesheet. "
"Images are exported to a folder with the same name as the exported &HTML; "
"file with <emphasis><filename>_files</filename></emphasis> appended."
msgstr ""
"&HTML; izvoz uporablja slogovno datoteko <filename>tellico2html.xsl</"
"filename>. Slike se izvozijo v mapo z enakim imenom kot izvoženi &HTML; "
"datoteka s pripetim <emphasis><filename>_files</filename></emphasis>."

#. Tag: para
#: importing-exporting.docbook:287
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The default format is similar to the printed output, and allows various "
"options for modifying the &HTML;. Field headers may be printed at the top of "
"each column, but unfortunately, &kde; does not yet allow the table headers "
"to be repeated on each page. The entries may be grouped as in the "
"<interface>Group View</interface>, as well."
msgstr ""
"Privzeti format je podoben natisnjenemu izhodu in omogoča različne možnosti "
"za spreminjanje &HTML;. Glave polj so lahko natisnjene na vrhu vsakega "
"stolpca, a na žalost &kde; še ne dovoljuje ponavljanja glav tabel na vsaki "
"strani. Vnose je mogoče združiti tudi v <interface>Group View</interface>."

#. Tag: para
#: importing-exporting.docbook:291
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Additionally, individual files may be created for each entry in the "
"collection, with links created in the top-level &HTML; file. The entry files "
"will be created in the same folder as the images. The entry &HTML; files "
"will use the current stylesheet template, as shown in the <interface>Entry "
"View</interface>."
msgstr ""
"Poleg tega se lahko za vsak vnos v zbirki ustvarijo posamezne datoteke s "
"povezavami, ustvarjenimi v zgornjem nivoju &HTML; mapa. Vnosne datoteke bodo "
"ustvarjene v isti mapi kot slike. Vnos &HTML; datoteke bodo uporabljale "
"trenutno predlogo slogovne datoteke, kot je prikazano v <interface>Vnosni "
"pogled</interface>."

#. Tag: screeninfo
#: importing-exporting.docbook:296
#, no-c-format
msgid "<screeninfo>&HTML; Export Options</screeninfo>"
msgstr "<screeninfo>&HTML; Možnosti izvoza</screeninfo>"

#. Tag: phrase
#: importing-exporting.docbook:299
#, no-c-format
msgid "<phrase>&HTML; Export Options</phrase>"
msgstr "<phrase>&HTML; Možnosti izvoza</phrase>"

#. Tag: title
#: importing-exporting.docbook:305
#, no-c-format
msgid "Exporting CSV"
msgstr "Izvažanje CSV"

#. Tag: para
#: importing-exporting.docbook:307
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Comma-separated values (CSV) are a common way of importing and exporting "
"tabular data. Each field value is separated by a comma, with one entry per "
"line. The field titles may be included as headers in the first line. Any "
"character or string other than a comma may also be used to delimit the "
"fields."
msgstr ""
"Vrednosti, ločene z vejico (CSV), so običajen način za uvoz in izvoz "
"tabelaričnih podatkov. Vsaka vrednost polja je ločena z vejico, z enim "
"vnosom na vrstico. Naslovi polj so lahko vključeni kot glave v prvi vrstici. "
"Za razmejitev polj se lahko uporabi tudi kateri koli znak ali niz, razen "
"vejice."

#. Tag: screeninfo
#: importing-exporting.docbook:312
#, no-c-format
msgid "<screeninfo>CSV Export Options</screeninfo>"
msgstr "<screeninfo>Možnosti izvoza CSV</screeninfo>"

#. Tag: phrase
#: importing-exporting.docbook:315
#, no-c-format
msgid "<phrase>CSV Export Options</phrase>"
msgstr "<phrase>Možnosti izvoza CSV</phrase>"

#. Tag: title
#: importing-exporting.docbook:321
#, no-c-format
msgid "Exporting Alexandria"
msgstr "Izvoz Alexandrie"

#. Tag: para
#: importing-exporting.docbook:323
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<application><ulink url=\"https://github.com/mvz/alexandria-book-collection-"
"manager\">Alexandria</ulink></application> is a book collection manager for "
"the <ulink url=\"http://www.gnome.org\">GNOME</ulink> desktop environment. "
"&appname; is able to export a limited subset of book collection fields to "
"the default Alexandria data location."
msgstr ""
"<application><ulink url=\"https://github.com/mvz/alexandria-book-collection-"
"manager\">Alexandria</ulink></application> je upravitelj knjižne zbirke za "
"<ulink url=\"http: //www.gnome.org\">GNOME</ulink> namizno okolje.&appname; "
"lahko izvozi omejeno podmnožico polj knjižne zbirke na privzeto lokacijo "
"podatkov Alexandria."

#. Tag: title
#: importing-exporting.docbook:330
#, no-c-format
msgid "Exporting ONIX"
msgstr "Izvažanje ONIX"

#. Tag: para
#: importing-exporting.docbook:332
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<ulink url=\"http://www.editeur.org/onix.html\">ONIX</ulink> is an &XML; "
"format for representing and communicating book industry product information, "
"primarily for book vendors. &appname; can export book collections using a "
"small subset of ONIX."
msgstr ""
"<ulink url=\"http://www.editeur.org/onix.html\">ONIX</ulink> je &XML; format "
"za predstavljanje in sporočanje informacij o izdelkih knjižne industrije, "
"predvsem za prodajalce knjig. &appname; lahko izvozi knjižne zbirke z majhno "
"podmnožico ONIX."

#. Tag: title
#: importing-exporting.docbook:339
#, no-c-format
msgid "Exporting Bibtex"
msgstr "Izvoz Bibtexa"

#. Tag: para
#: importing-exporting.docbook:341
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"When exporting to <ulink url=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Bibtex\">Bibtex</"
"ulink>, the field values may be escaped with braces or quotation marks. If "
"any string macros are used in the collection, they may optionally be "
"exported as macros or expanded. For &URL; fields, &appname; may enclose the "
"field values with the <literal>\\url{...}</literal> tag. Finally, entries "
"with no citation key may be skipped rather than have &appname; auto-generate "
"the key."
msgstr ""
"Pri izvozu v <ulink url=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Bibtex\">Bibtex</"
"ulink> so lahko vrednosti polj označene z oklepaji ali narekovaji. Če so v "
"zbirki uporabljeni makri nizov, jih je mogoče po želji izvoziti kot makre "
"ali razširiti. Za &URL; polja lahko &appname; obdaja vrednosti polja z "
"oznako <literal>\\\\url{...}</literal>. Nazadnje, vnose brez ključa navedbe "
"lahko preskočite, namesto da bi imeli &appname; samodejno ustvari ključ."

#. Tag: screeninfo
#: importing-exporting.docbook:348
#, no-c-format
msgid "<screeninfo>Bibtex Export Options</screeninfo>"
msgstr "<screeninfo>Možnosti izvoza Bibtex</screeninfo>"

#. Tag: phrase
#: importing-exporting.docbook:351
#, no-c-format
msgid "<phrase>Bibtex Export Options</phrase>"
msgstr "<phrase>Možnosti izvoza Bibtex</phrase>"

#. Tag: title
#: importing-exporting.docbook:357
#, no-c-format
msgid "Exporting GCstar"
msgstr "Izvoz GCstar"

#. Tag: para
#: importing-exporting.docbook:359
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<application><ulink url=\"http://www.gcstar.org\">GCstar</ulink></"
"application> is another movie collection manager. &appname; is able to "
"export most collection types to a GCstar data file."
msgstr ""
"<application><ulink url=\"http://www.gcstar.org\">GCstar</ulink></"
"application> je še en upravitelj zbirke filmov. &appname; lahko izvozi "
"večino vrst zbirk v podatkovno datoteko GCstar."

#. Tag: title
#: importing-exporting.docbook:366
#, no-c-format
msgid "Exporting &XML; via &xslt;"
msgstr "Izvažanje &XML; prek &xslt;"

#. Tag: para
#: importing-exporting.docbook:368
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Finally, &appname; is able to process its internal &XML; representation of "
"the collection data through an external &XSL; stylesheet before exporting. "
"This type of export may be useful for generating text reports or other file "
"types."
msgstr ""
"Končno &appname; lahko obdela svoj notranji &XML; predstavitev podatkov o "
"zbirki prek zunanjega &XSL; pred izvozom. Ta vrsta izvoza je lahko uporabna "
"za ustvarjanje besedilnih poročil ali drugih vrst datotek."

#. Tag: title
#: importing-exporting.docbook:376
#, no-c-format
msgid "Working With Citations"
msgstr "Delo s citati"

#. Tag: para
#: importing-exporting.docbook:377
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"When working with a <link linkend=\"bibliography\">bibliography</link>, "
"citations for the currently selected entries may be generated and used in "
"various other applications. A citation in bibtex format can be copied to the "
"clipboard, and then pasted in a latex file. Bibtex citations can also be "
"pushed to an external application such as <application>LyX</application> or "
"<application>Kile</application> using the so-called <emphasis><link linkend="
"\"hidden-bibtex-options\">lyxpipe</link></emphasis>."
msgstr ""
"Pri delu z <link linkend=\"bibliography\">bibliografijo</link> se lahko "
"ustvarijo citati za trenutno izbrane vnose in uporabijo v različnih drugih "
"aplikacijah. Navedbo v formatu bibtex je mogoče kopirati v odložišče in nato "
"prilepiti v datoteko iz lateksa. Navedbe Bibtex je mogoče potisniti tudi v "
"zunanjo aplikacijo, kot je <application>LyX</application> ali "
"<application>Kile</application> s tako imenovanim <emphasis><link linkend="
"\"hidden-bibtex-options\">lyxpipe </link></emphasis>."
